text: St. Antönien is a Swiss village in the Prättigau and a former municipality in the district of Prättigau/Davos in the canton of Graubünden. The former municipality of St. Antönien Ascharina merged on 1 January 2007 into St. Antönien. The municipality of St. Antönien on 1 January 2016 merged into Luzein. == Other websites == * Official website Category:Villages in Graubünden Category:Former municipalities of Graubünden Category:2016 disestablishments in Switzerland
